Introduction

Vahn is a South Korean rapper, singer-songwriter, and producer under FirstOne Entertainment. He is a member of the boy group NINE.i and a former member of the pre-debut groups UTH, HNB, and YOURS.

2018: Under Nineteen On October 25, Jungwoo was introduced as a contestant of Under Nineteen with his moving poster. He was part of the vocal team and was eliminated in the twelfth episode after achieving 10th place in the vocal team.

2019–2020: UTH On December 26, he was introduced as a member of the pre-debut group UTH. They presumably disbanded in 2020 as their social media has been inactive since 2019.

2020: YOURS Sometime in 2020, his personal Instagram bio mentioned he was a Kpop trainee under Deep Studio Entertainment, along with his fellow member from UTH, Sejin. They both left the group in July.

2022: NINE.i On January 10, 2022, he was introduced as a member of the pre-debut group NINE.i. They debuted on March 30, 2022, with the mini album New World.

2024: "Crush On You" On July 16, 2024, Vahn announced his first digital single, "Crush On You," which will be released on July 20.
